sayistische und poetische Auseinandersetzungen zur politischen Gestaltung Deutschlands nach Ende des Zweiten Weltkriegs und des Nationalsozialismus: Welche ästhetischen Linien lassen sich von der Weimarer Republik über das Exil bis in die frühe BRD verfolgen? Welche Bedeutung kommt Thomas Mann und seinem Werk in Ost und West zu? Wie verortet sich der Autor politisch und an welche Denktraditionen knüpft er an?  aThis volume discusses Thomas Mann’s essayistic and poetic engagement with Germany’s political configuration after the end of the Second World War and National Socialism. Can any aesthetic continuities be traced from the Weimar Republic, through exile, to the early FRG? What was the significance of Thomas Mann and his work in East and West? How did the author position himself politically, and which traditions of thought did he take up?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 4aExil. 4aMann, Thomas. 4aNachkriegszeit. 4aOst-West. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aEast-West.  aThomas Mann.  aexile.  apost-war period.1 aBischoff, Doerte, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoes, Tobias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aElsaghe, Yahya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHacke, Jens, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKemper, Dirk, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKinder, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKinder, Anna, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLenhard, Philipp, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLörke, Tim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLörke, Tim, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/